column43: PRINTING INK, FLAMMABLE OR PRINTING INK RELATED MATERIAL (INCLUDING PRINTING INK THINNING OR REDUCING COMPOUND), FLAMMABLE
column169: On January 3, 2024, one (1) 55-gallon drum of printing ink was forked and released approximately 55-gallons to the dodck floor. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched crews from First Call Environmental (FCE) and Thin Line Environmental (TLE) to remediate the impacted site. R+L deployed absorbents prior to their arrival. FCE utilized hand tools to collect the absorbents. All UN1210 impacted material was collected and containerized in one (1) 85-gallon drum, one (1) 55-gallon drum, and four (4) 95-gallon overpacks. TLE personnel aided in transferring all non-damaged product to new, undamaged pallets for continued shipment.

column43: PAINT INCLUDING PAINT, LACQUER, ENAMEL, STAIN, SHELLAC SOLUTIONS, VARNISH, POLISH, LIQUID FILLER AND LIQUID LACQUER BASE
column169: XPO Logistics contacted ERTS regarding one leaking 55-gallon DM containing hazardous product, RDL44LVOC. A contractor dispatched and observed an estimated 1-gallon release onto the wooden trailer floor in a 2’ x 3’ area as a result of improper packaging. Oil dry was applied to the release and the damaged, leaking drum was overpacked. Two drums were generated container the overpacked drum of product, the impacted oil dry and the impacted PPE. XPO will manage all waste generated from the response. No storm-drains, waterways, or soil were involved in this incident.
